When a SQL_EXCEPTION exception occurs in a transaction, this options processes as normal SQL when a specific string is included in the exception message.

The following is an example of SQLException.

    java.sql.SQLException: JDBC-0000: Error ...
    ...


When the above exception occurs, the exception message("JDBC-0000" or "Error ...") can registerto handle exception as normal message. 

If the option is set, SQL_EXCEPTION errors and events in transaction data are ignored.

---

* Default : No
* Type : String
* Restart: Not required
* Version supported : 5.4.3.9, 5.5.2